{
  "id": "bundle-session-ontology",
  "name": "Session Ontology",
  "category": "Bundles",
  "description": "The card-game ontology built over one session. A loop tree (Game > Run > {Setup, Wander > Happening > Battle > Round > Turn}) doubles as a scope spine: every element declares the lifetime it introduces, and a type's full scope is the union of its own SCOPED_TO plus all scopes inherited via IS. Cards are immutable definitions; Prints bear no attributes and diverge only by the Mods applied to them. Mods are guarded rewrites (APPLIES_TO a Moddable, MODIFIES an Attribute, FROM a guard value, TO a result) with no write-event and no history — a Value is the accumulation of the Mods in scope for it. Location is an Attribute, so movement is attribute-mutation and needs no special machinery. Contains no patterns and no implications: the ontology is only triples.",
